post_title_1: Iraq may need to justify OPEC fudge: Fuel for Thought
post_content_1: Iraq is compliant with neither the spirit nor the letter of the OPEC-led agreement to cut oil production from January 1 this year. The question is whether it should be. With OPEC and non-OPEC technical experts set to meet to discuss faltering conformity, OPEC’s second largest producer may feel more than justified in its position, but among members those claims have a hollow ring.

post_title_3: Venezuelan army hunts armed rebels after military base attacked
post_content_3: Venezuela's military says it is hunting 10 armed members of a "terrorist" gang who escaped after attacking a major base in the northwest of the country.
